abstract: Ningbo Port fell in its Shanghai debut, after China’s third-largest port operator raised $1.1 billion in the country’s sixth-biggest initial public offering this year.
snippet: Ningbo Port fell in its Shanghai debut, after China’s third-largest port operator raised $1.1 billion in the country’s sixth-biggest initial public offering this year.
lead_paragraph: Ningbo Port, China’s third-largest port operator, fell as much as 2.7 percent in its Shanghai debut on fears of limited growth potential, after it raised $1.1 billion in China’s sixth-biggest initial public offering this year.

headline.main: Ningbo Port Shares Sink in Shanghai Debut
